Lipolysis rates (%) of individual triacylglycerol (TAG) species in soybean oil (SBO) and pomegranate seed oil (PGO) after 30 min of digestion in the simulated model of small intestinal digestion. Statistical differences are indicated by letters where significant differences were detected (
   p < 0.1 for A and B; 
   p < 0.05 for a and b). Abbreviation: P, palmitic acid; S, stearic acid; O, oleic acid; L, linoleic acid; Ln, linolenic acid; CLn, conjugated linolenic acid.
